Subject: [PATCH] patch 0884: Movers 3-pillar peer-sympathy gate + hypothesis
 tiers
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Per user mechanism-engine audit: "Do NOT declare peer-sympathy unless
correlated stocks move with same direction, time window, volume
co-movement. Every reason must have probability tiers: PRIMARY /
SECONDARY / REJECTED."

PeerBucket extended with pctsUp / pctsDown / volsUp / volsDown arrays
so the gate can compute peer magnitude median + volume co-movement
ratio across same-direction peers (was only counting bodies before).

3-pillar peer-sympathy validation (all four must pass):
  1. peer count       : >=4 in sector, >=2 same-direction, ratio >=0.65
  2. peer magnitude   : median peer move >= 0.35x of this stock move
                        (a 20% mover needs peers averaging 7%+)
  3. peer volume      : >=50% of same-direction peers vol >=1.3x 20D
                        (proves coincident accumulation/distribution)
  4. sector outperf   : sector |delta vs index| >= 1.0pp

If ANY pillar fails, peer-sympathy is REJECTED. Each failure records
explicit reason ("peer count 1/4 ratio 0.25 < 0.65 floor"; "peer
median 4.2% << this 18.0%"; "only 1/3 peers showed vol co-movement").
Engine falls through to liquidity-vacuum / operator-rotation
fallback with mechanism = LIQUIDITY_VACUUM.

fuseCausalNarrative output extended with primary / secondary /
rejected fields. The detail string (shown in row tooltip) now reads:
  "PRIMARY: <strongest signal phrase> · SECONDARY: <next> ·
   REJECTED: peer-sympathy (ratio 0.43 < 0.65 floor; only 1/4 peers
   showed vol co-movement)"
- per user spec: "Every reason must have probability tiers: PRIMARY
(most likely) · SECONDARY (supporting) · REJECTED (explicitly ruled
out)".

For BLISSGVS +20%: previous engine emitted "Peer-sympathy momentum"
because 2 of 4 pharma peers were up. New engine checks:
  - peer median pct: probably ~3% (much less than 20% / 0.35 = 7%)
  - peer vol co-move: probably <50%
  - rejection logged: REJECTED peer-sympathy (peer median 3.0% << this
    20.0%; only 0/2 peers showed vol co-movement)
  - falls through to LIQUIDITY_VACUUM with honest sentence:
    "thin-float expansion (liquidity-driven) - no confirmed peer cluster"
